{"lemma":"دُونُ","slug":"دُونُ","root":"د.#.ن","root_slug":"د-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/د-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دُون","root":"دون","pos":"N","occurrence_count":144},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","adv","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13500"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"low, base, inferior"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"below"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"below","examples":[{"text":"«فَأْتُوا بِالتَّوْرَاةِ فَاتْلُوهَا إِنْ كُنْتُمْ صَادِقِينَ!» – فَوَضَعَ مِدْرَاسُهَا الَّذِي يُدَرِّسُهَا مِنْهُمْ كَفَّهُ عَلَى آيَةِ الرَّجْمِ، فَطَفِقَ يَقْرَأُ مَا دُونَ يَدِهِ وَمَا وَرَاءَهَا، وَلَا يَقْرَأُ آيَةَ الرَّجْمِ.","english":"“Bring the Torah here and recite it if ye art truthful!” – and the teacher teaching it put the palm of his hand over the stoning verse and commenced to read what was [written] below and what [from his point of view] behind his hand, not reading the stoning verse."}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"less than","examples":[{"text":"والكتم قال أبو الخير هو ثلاثة أنواع منها ما له ورق عريض مثل ورق الآس الذي ينبت في الشعرى وهو يعلو كثيرا ويأخذ من التدويح وورقه مشرفة مثل تشريف المنشار ومنه نوع آخر له ورق دون الأول في العرض وتعظم شجرته أيضا وله حب في قدر حب الفلفل والريحان ويعتصر منه دهن يستصبح به ونوع آخر له ورق طويل دقيق مثل ورق المسان وقيل إن مما جرب فصح إنه إن سقى من عصارة ورقه ثمانية دراهم لمن عضه الكلب فإنه يبرئ في ذلك اليوم ويخلص بإذن الله تعالى وأن فزع من الماء فإنه يبرئ والكتم هو شبيه للحناء ويجفف ورقه ويدق نعما ويخلط بالحناء وخضب به الشعر.","english":"About the mock privet says Abū al-Ḵayr that there are three kinds of it: The first has wide leaves similar to the leaves of the myrtle which grows in the maquis and it becomes very high and swollen and its leaves are humped like a saw, the second has leaves of lesser width but its tree is also poddy and its seeds are of the size of the seeds of peppers and myrtles and from them one can press oil for lighting, and another kind has long delicate leaves like sandpaper and it is said if someone is affected by scabies then he will regain health, that if he whom a dog has bitten drinks eight dirhem from the extract of its leaves he will becomes free from the ailment the same day and cleansed of it if God is gracious; so that he will fear water but he will be free of the pest. Mock privet is similar to henna and one dries its leaves and crushes them well and mixes with henna and dyes the hair with it."}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"other than","examples":[{"text":"وَنَحْسُدُ أنْ نَزُورَكُمُ وَنَرْضَى / بِدُونِ الْبَذْلِ لَوْ عَلِمَ الْحَسُودُ"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"behind"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"without"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to record, to write down"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Developed from the root د ن و (d n w) denoting being lower, to come close or near before something, at their feet; cognate with Aramaic דני (“to prostrate, to lower oneself to or before a higher authority, to humble”).\n\nDenominal verb of دِيوَان (dīwān, “register”)."},"ipa":["/duːn/","/duː.na/","/daw.wa.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13500","headword_ar":"دُونً","root":"dwn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Low, base, vile, mean, paltry, inconsiderable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contemptible;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, T, S, M, * Msb, K;) applied to a man &c.: (T, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inferior,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower, baser, viler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in grounds of pretension to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any approvable quality"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Lth, T:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as falls short"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a thing]; used in this sense as a prefixed noun: (Ham p. 686:) [see below what is said of its usage as a prefixed noun by Lth and by Sb: and used as an epithet,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scanty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deficient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to anything:] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a middling sort; between good and bad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man and to a commodity: (M:) and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminent, in rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition; noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honourable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:) thus it bears two contr. significations (K) [and significations intermediate between those two]. A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA maA EalaA Almaro'u raAma AlEalaA='\n                      \n                     \n                        wayaqotaEu biAld~uwni mano kaAnaA duwnaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the man is high"},{"kind":"text","text":"in rank, or nobility,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he seeks highness: and he who is low is content with that which is low"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) Accord. to the most common usage, (Msb,) or accord. to what is asserted to be the most common usage, (Lh, M,) one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN mino duwnK","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ مِنْ دُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N mino duwnK","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ مِنْ دُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a kind that is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low, base,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a kind that is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low, base,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (Msb:) but sometimes they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN duwnN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ دُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N duwnN","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ دُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN duwnN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ دُونٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bad"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an inferior"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN duwnN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ دُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, K;) for the Arabs did not use this phrase. (T.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Accord."},{"kind":"text","text":"to Lth, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA duwnu *aAka","text_ar":"هٰذَا دُونُ ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the inferior of that"},{"kind":"text","text":"], when meaning to denote by it low estimation, using the nom. case: (T:) [but this is uncommon, if allowable:] Sb says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwn","text_ar":"دُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not used in the nom. case as a prefixed noun: as to the saying in the Kur [lxxii. 11, an instance similar to which occurs also in vii. 167],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min~aA","text_ar":"مِنَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aAliHuwna wa min~aA duwna *`lika","text_ar":"الصَّالِحُونَ وَ مِنَّا دُونَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa min~aA","text_ar":"وَ مِنَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN duwna *`lika","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ دُونَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of us are the righteous, and of us are a party below that party in rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, TA;) or, as another says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dwn","text_ar":"دون"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here in the accus. case but in the place of a noun in the nom. case because it is generally used as an adv. n. (TA.) ―         -b2-  As an adv. n.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwn","text_ar":"دُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Below,"},{"kind":"text","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoq","text_ar":"فَوْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as denoting a falling short of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"denoting low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean, estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a condition lower, baser, viler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than that of another, in grounds of pretension to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any approvable quality"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Lth, T;) [and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inferior to, beneath, under,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"short of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"another"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in rank, height, size,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less than"},{"kind":"text","text":"another, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more deficient than"},{"kind":"text","text":"another: (Fr, T:) and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoq","text_ar":"فَوْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in highness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminence, of rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in nobility;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;) [and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeding"},{"kind":"text","text":"another, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more than"},{"kind":"text","text":"another:] thus bearing two contr. significations. (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN duwnaka","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ دُونَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a condition lower, baser, viler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than thine, in grounds of pretension to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]: and when one says, “ Verily such a one is high, or eminent, in rank or condition, ” or “ is noble, ” another replies,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa duwna *`lika","text_ar":"وَ دُونَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And above that."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beneath, below in situation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"under;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHot","text_ar":"تَحْت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, TA.) Using it in this sense, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwan qadamika xad~u Eaduw~ika","text_ar":"دُوَن قَدَمِكَ خَدُّ عَدُوِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May the cheek of thine enemy be beneath thy foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasa duwnahu","text_ar":"جَلَسَ دُونَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sat below him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Before in respect of place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in front:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [the contr., namely,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K.) [You may say, using it in the former sense,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasa duwnahu","text_ar":"جَلَسَ دُونَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sat before him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in front of him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see Ham p. 86:) and, using it in the latter sense,] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^amiyrN EalaY maA duwna","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَمِيرٌ عَلَى مَا دُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayoHuwna","text_ar":"جَيْحُونَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This"},{"kind":"text","text":"[man]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is governor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prince, over what is beyond"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the river]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jeyhoon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabol","text_ar":"قَبْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Before in respect of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of place also,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which may perhaps be here meant]: (T:) and [the contr., namely,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEod","text_ar":"بَعْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after in respect of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but as"},{"kind":"page_break","n":939},{"kind":"text","text":"some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of place"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, which may perhaps be here meant]. (Fr, T, TA.) ―         -b6-  It signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nearer than"},{"kind":"text","text":"another thing: (S, Msb, K:) so in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA duwna *`lika","text_ar":"هٰذَا دُونَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is nearer than that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S Msb;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA duwnahu","text_ar":"هٰذَا دُونَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is nearer than he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) [Hence,] one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Audonu duwnaka","text_ar":"اُدْنُ دُونَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Draw thou near in the space that is between me and thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A Heyth, T:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approach thou nearer to me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"draw thou near"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearer"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaziydu baguD~u AlT~arofa duwniY","text_ar":"يَزِيدُ بَغُضُّ الطَّرْفَ دُونِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", a saying of a poet, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Yezeed lowers the eye towards a spot between me and him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A Heyth, T.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$aEato","text_ar":"خَشَعَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnahu AlA^aboSaAru","text_ar":"دُونَهُ الاَبْصَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, has a similar meaning: see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"x$E","text_ar":"خشع"},{"kind":"text","text":". So, too, has the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAwata Tarofahu","text_ar":"خَاوَتَ طَرْفَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwniY","text_ar":"دُونِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 3 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xwt","text_ar":"خوت"},{"kind":"text","text":". And hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwna Aln~ahori jamaAEapN","text_ar":"دُونَ النَّهْرِ جَمَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the way of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, the river,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on this side of the river,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearer than the river, is a company of men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before thy reaching the river"},{"kind":"text","text":"[there is to be found, or encountered,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwna qatoli","text_ar":"دُونَ قَتْلِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asadi A^ahowaAlN","text_ar":"الاَسَدِ اَهْوَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the way of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, the slaying of the lion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before thine attaining to the slaying of the lion, terrors"},{"kind":"text","text":"[are to be encountered]. (T, TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnahu xaroTu AlqataAdi","text_ar":"دُونَهُ خَرْطُ القَتَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrT","text_ar":"خرط"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAla duwna Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"حَالَ دُونَ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It intervened as an obstacle in the way to the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it prevented from attaining the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(W p. 71.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa duwnahu","text_ar":"لَيْسَ دُونَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is nothing intervening as an obstacle in the way of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And [hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qutila duwna maAlihi","text_ar":"قُتِلَ دُونَ مَالِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosihi","text_ar":"نَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axiyhi","text_ar":"اَخِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaArihi","text_ar":"جَارِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was slain in defence of his property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his brother,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his neighbour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Occurring in a trad. commencing with the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algariyqu $ahiydN","text_ar":"الغَرِيقُ شَهِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the “ Jámi' es-Sagheer, ” and thus explained in the margin of a copy of that work.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaHa duwnahu","text_ar":"نَبَحَ دُونَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a modern phrase meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He defended him as though by barking in the way to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b7-  [Hence,] also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Against;"},{"kind":"text","text":"denoting defence by means of intervention: see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axoSN","text_ar":"شَخْصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Fr, T, TA.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda","text_ar":"عِنْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At, near, nigh, by,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near by; with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"present with;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Fr, T, Ibn-Es-Seed.) Accord. to Ez-Zowzanee, it has this meaning in the saying of Imra-el-Keys, [describing a horse,]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faA^aloHaqanaA biAlhaAdiyaAti wa duwnahu\n                      \n                     \n                        jawaAHiruhaA fiY Sar~apK lamo tuzay~ali"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, but only the former hemistich is there given,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he made us to overtake the foremost"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the wild animals,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"while near to him were those that lagged behind, in a herd, not dispersed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(EM p. 48.) ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayor","text_ar":"غَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Other than, beside,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"besides, exclusively of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not"},{"kind":"text","text":"as used before a substantive or an adjective]. (K.) Hence, in the Kur [xxi. 82],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayaEomaluwna EamalFA duwna","text_ar":"وَيَعْمَلُونَ عَمَلًا دُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And"},{"kind":"text","text":"who"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"should do work other than,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beside, that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Fr, TA.) And in the same [iv. 51 and 116],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayagofiru maA duwna *`lika","text_ar":"وَيَغْفِرُ مَا دُونَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But He will forgive what is other than that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is less than that."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.) And so, it is said, in the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa fiymaA duwna xamosi A^awaAqK","text_ar":"لَيْسَ فِيمَا دُونَ خَمْسِ اَوَاقٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaqapN","text_ar":"صَدَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no poor-rate"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be exacted"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the case of what is other than,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less than, five ounces"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) So, too, it is said to mean in the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajaAza AlxuloEa duwna EiqaASi raA^osihaA","text_ar":"اَجَازَ الخُلْعَ دُونَ عِقَاصِ رَاْسِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He allowed the divorcing a wife for a gift,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compensation, other than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqaAS","text_ar":"عِقَاص"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of her head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK, in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaloEu","text_ar":"الخَلْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxuloEa","text_ar":"الخُلْعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", this is given as an ex. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uwna","text_ar":"ذُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawiY","text_ar":"سَوِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayor","text_ar":"غَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for anything, even for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EqAS","text_ar":"عقاص"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of her head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b10-  It is also used (M, K, TA) as a subst. (M, TA) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to it, [very often in this case, in the Kur and elsewhere, as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayor","text_ar":"غَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes in other senses explained above,] and likewise with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,) though rarely. (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA duwnaka","text_ar":"هٰذَا دُونَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA mino duwnika","text_ar":"هٰذَا مِنْ دُونِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is below thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (M, TA.) And it is said in the Kur [xxviii. 23],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wawajada mino duwnihimu A@moraA^atayoni","text_ar":"وَوَجَدَ مِنْ دُونِهِمُ ا@مْرَاَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he found in a place below them two women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beside them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exclusively of them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`daA liYduwna laka","text_ar":"هٰدَا لِىدُونَ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino duwnika","text_ar":"مِنْ دُونِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This belongs to me exclusively of thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou hast no right nor share"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in this."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 186.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhimo mano layosa","text_ar":"فِيهِمْ مَنْ لَيْسَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biduwnihi","text_ar":"بِدُونِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Among whom was such as was not below him"},{"kind":"text","text":"in respect of knowledge of poetry] is used by Akh in his book on rhymes. (M, TA.) ―         -b11-  It also denotes a command, (T, K,) and an incitement (Fr, T, S, K) to do a thing. (S.) Using it in the former sense,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnaka Ald~irohama","text_ar":"دُونَكَ الدِّرْهَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou the dirhem;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnaka Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"دُونَكَ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnaka biAl$~aYo'i","text_ar":"دُونَكَ بِالشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou the thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and using it in the latter sense, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnakahu","text_ar":"دُونَكَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep thou, cleave thou, cling thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hold thou fast, to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"take care of him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dunaka zayodFA","text_ar":"دُنَكَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to Zeyd, taking care of him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) Temeem [meaning a party of the tribe so named] said to El-Hajjáj, when he had slain, i. e. crucified, Sálih Ibn-' Abd-Er-Rahmán, “ Permit us to bury Sálih: ” and he replied,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnakumuwhu","text_ar":"دُونَكُمُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take ye him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b12-  And it also denotes a threat. (T, K.) So in the sayings"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwaka SiraAEiY","text_ar":"دُوَكَ صِرَاعِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beware thou of wrestling with me"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnaka fatamar~aso biY","text_ar":"دُونَكَ فَتَمَرَّسْ بِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beware thou, and then set thyself against me to do evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"if thou canst]. (T, TA.) ―         -b13-  It is said that no verb is derived from it: (T, S, M, Msb:) but some assert that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAna","text_ar":"دَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^udiyna","text_ar":"اُدِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[mentioned in the first paragraph of this art.] are derived from it. (S.) ―         -b14-  The dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwna","text_ar":"دُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwayona","text_ar":"دُوَيْنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 404:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwayonapa","text_ar":"دُوَيْنَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs as a dim. in a verse of a post-classical poet; but, [ISd says,] of what word I know not, unless they said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnapa","text_ar":"دُونَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwna","text_ar":"دُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["T","Msb","Lth","M","K","Lh","Fr","TA","S","Bd"]}]}}